On Mon, 13 Sep 1999, Jens Benecke wrote:
> How does windows find these infos? Normally it doesn't even look for it. I
> have yet to see a Windows fresh install that does _not_ come up in
> 640x480x16.
For the most part Windows gets driver config data from .inf files supplied
as part of the driver installation. 
It is not unknown for these settings to completely bollocks up a PC as
they rarely consider that the PC will already have other hardware and
Windows is none too good at handling conflicts.
